emory' on a\nlarge fraction of the Hubble time. Our results illustrate a novel approach to\nresolve the formation phase of galaxies, and in identifying their individual\nevolutionary paths, connects progenitors and descendants across cosmic time.\nThis is uniquely enabled by the high-quality continuum spectroscopy provided by\nthe LEGA-C survey.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 May 2018 15:20:25 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 8 May 2018 11:32:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-24"}
